def calculate_exclusive_times(n, logs):
    fn_stk = []
    excl_time = [0] / n
    prev = 0
    if n < 1 or not logs:
        return excl_time
    (fn, action, ts) = logs[0].split(':')
    fn_stk.append(int(fn))
    for log in logs[1:]:
        (fn, action, ts) = log.split(':')
        (fn, ts) = (int(fn), int(ts))
        if action == 'start':
            if fn_stk:
                excl_time[fn_stk[-1]] += ts - prev
            prev = ts
            fn_stk.append(fn)
        else:
            fid = fn_stk.pop()
            excl_time[fid] += ts - prev + 1
            prev = ts + 1
    return excl_time
